               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="188003010151"></xptr>
               <p>said "He can and will find them for you, but he would want something for his trouble"—he said that an attachment ought to be put on Mrs. Rose's income—it was not for me to follow up these Roses after we found they had gone—he named Mrs. Rose's bank as King and Co.—I did not go there—it was no use—it is their rule not to answer inquiries.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Re-examined.</hi> Some of the neighbours told me that the house had been empty for about six months, and it had every appearance of that.</p>
