                  </hi>. I am landlord of the premises 6, Three Crowns Square, Borough—in September, 1878, I let two rooms on the second floor to a man named Gourlay, at a rent of 30<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. a year—shortly afterwards I saw the name of Gear and Co. on one of the doors and Laird and Co. on the other—I had no dealings with Gear—I think I got about 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. rent about 15 months ago—I think there was about nine or 10 months due when Laird was arrested—the rent was to be paid monthly</p>
