               <p>—about a week after I had let the premises I noticed on the outside door' "British and Foreign Bank"—I told Gourlay I could not have that; it must be painted out, as it seemed to me so inconsistent with a bank on the second floor—he said he would do so—it went over for some short time and it was not done, and I had it done—he told me that he had correspondents at Hamburg, and they liked a bank to make their bills payable at—I think there was something painted on the panel of the room door upstairs—I don't recollect whether I saw it myself or wag told of it—I gave directions to have that painted out, and it was painted out.</p>
