                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. TORR</hi>. de Jough was my traveller—I wrote two or three memorandums to Lindsay and Co.—the value of the proposed order was 35<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.; they did not offer to pay cash, they offered to pay in 14 days; the value of the corn flour was 40<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 50<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—Laird said he had some wine to sell on commission, if I liked he would make an exchange.</p>
